    <statement>
        <p>
            Given the vector equation <m>\hat{ w }(t)=\langle \frac{4}{5} \cdot 3^{t}, -\frac{1}{3} \, t \rangle</m>:
            
            <ol>
                <li>Write this equation as parametric equations .</li>
                <li>Sketch the graph of the corresponding curve.</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
        
    </statement>
    <answer>
            <m>x(t)=\frac{4}{5} \cdot 3^{t}, y(t)=-\frac{1}{3} \, t</m>.
    </answer>
